==English==
===Etymology===
Middle English ''[[ugge]]'' from Icelandic ''[[ugga]]'' fear
===Variant spelling===
*[[ugg]]
===Intransitive verb===
'''to ug'''  (''transitive'' and ''intransitive'')
# {{Obsolete)) To [[feel]] [[dread]], [[loathing]] or [[disgust]].
# {{Obsolete)) To fear, feel [[horror]]; [[shudder]] with horror

===Transitive verb===
# {{rfv-sense}} To [[abhor]], [[loathe]] or [[detest]] something or someone.
# {{rfv-sense}} To fill someone with [[dread]], [[loathing]] or [[disgust]].

===Noun===
# {{Obsolete)) fear, horror
# ''(Provincial English):'' A [[surfeit]]

